-- Colombian Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Canacol Energy Increase
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-31T15:46:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/colombian-stock-movers-ecopetrol-canacol-energy-increase.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:04 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.4 percent to 13,816.12, while the
Colcap Index advanced 0.2 percent to 1,617.01.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  Colombia , gained 0.3 percent to
1,630 pesos. Interbolsa SA, Colombia’s biggest brokerage,
changed its recommendation from “hold” to “speculative buy”
after the stock fell 55 percent in 2011, the worst performance
on Colombia’s IGBC benchmark index. Interbolsa set a year-end
target price of 2,138 pesos, according to an e-mailed report
today by analyst Juan David Pineros.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 0.3 percent to 4,600 pesos. RCN radio said yesterday the
company’s profit rose to about 14 trillion pesos ($7.8 billion)
in 2011, leading the government to consider postponing a sale of
a stake in Ecopetrol. Bogota-based RCN didn’t say where it
obtained the information. Ecopetrol said in a statement that
fourth-quarter earnings aren’t yet available.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  